title: Oakwood's Rowe ends up fifth in IHSA State Golf Meet
text:
Deb Edwards/Commercial-News Oakwood's Rowe ends up fifth in IHSA State Golf Meet 
Deb Edwards | Commercial-NewsOakwood’s Rhylee Kerst and Shelby Mascari jump to block a shot by Salt Fork’s Katie Witte during Saturday’s game at the Vermilion County Tournament. The Comets won 25-20, 25-19 and won all of their matches to make Monday’s County Championship against Armstrong-Potomac.   Oakwood's Rowe ends up fifth in IHSA State Golf Meet STAFF REPORT   
NORMAL — With another strong finish, Oakwood’s Brandon Rowe ended up taking fifth place on Saturday at the IHSA Class 1A Boys Golf Meet at Prarie Vista Golf Course. 
The junior, who was fifth going into the final round, rallied with a par and two birdies in the final three holes to go from ninth place to fifth. 
“I was a little nervous because I wanted to do well and it got to me at the start,” Rowe said. “I came back and hit a few putts that I really needed at the end. 
“It’s great. I have been working on this my whole life and this has been everything I can ever ask for.” 
With the finish, Rowe finishes a season where he was at or near the top of most of the meets he was in. 
“I had a good season and was able to keep my score in the 70’s,” Rowe said. “I just wanted to translate that into playing in state and see how it would stand up.” 
Rowe said he has already completed a major goal with the finish and with one more season left, he wants to do even more. 
“I wanted to always finish in the top 10 in state and it was great to get that,” Rowe said. “Now I want to get better in the summer and try to get the win.” 
The Bismarck-Henning golf team did a little better in the second round, shooting a 363 as a team to take 10th at 729. 
Hunter Keith led the way with a 86 for Bismarck-Henning, while Cade Herriott had a 91, Skyler Mitchell had a 92, Kade Smith had a 94, Blake Douglass scored a 96 and Jake Sermersheim had a 116. 
Elgin St. Edward’s Michael Mattas won the individual title with a total score of 149 while Byron won the team title with a score of 658. 
PREP CROSS COUNTRY 
Danville boys second in Big 12 
PEORIA — Carl Way was second with a time of 15 minutes 24 seconds as the Vikings took second as a team as the Vikings took second at the Big 12 Conference meet in Detweiler Park. 
William Powell was fourth for Danville (15:43), while Philip Hall was 10th (15:56), Tyler Huckelberry was 20th (16:38), Brandon Barfell was 26th (16:44) and Jeremiah Cooley took 27th (16:45). 
In the girls race, Sadie Elliott was fifth with a time of 18 minutes, 18 seconds as Danville was fourth as a team. Dezerai Huckelberry was 19th (19:59), Shreja Patel was 33rd (21:02, Esperanza Torres was 34th (21:19) and Madison Smith was 47th (22:14). 
PREP VOLLEYBALL 
Oakwood, A-P reach county final 
OAKWOOD — The Comets won three matches and the Trojans took two to advance to Monday’s Vermilion County Tournament final. 
Oakwood beat Hoopeston Area 25-4, 25-6, Salt Fork 25-20, 25-19 and Georgetown-Ridge Farm 25-21, 25-12 while Armstrong-Potomac beat Bismarck-Henning 25-21, 25-23 and Westville 25-22, 15-25, 25-23. 
Holley Hamleton had 13 kills and 39 digs for the Trojans, while Ashley Gayheart had nine kills and 41 digs and Makenzie Vinson had seven kills, 27 assists and 31 digs. 
Westville would rebound to beat Bismarck-Henning 14-25, 31-29, 25-23 to advance to the third place game against Salt Fork, who beat Georgetown-Ridge Farm 25-17, 25-16 and Hoopeston Area 25-14, 25-17. 
Mariah Rolinitis had 13 kills, two blocks and 38 digs for the Tigers, while Morgan Gallion had 22 assists, Adriannie Pate had 15 assists, five kills and 26 digs, Krista Smith had eight kills, six aces and 38 digs and Riley Kinney had 13 kills and four blocks. 
The Buffaloes defeated Hoopeston Area 25-11, 25-13 and will play the Blue Devils for fifth place on Monday at 5 p.m. Hadley Goodwin had 21 kills and 27 digs, while Lacey Steinbaugh had 46 assists and Cassandra Goodwin had seven blocks. 
The third place game will be on Monday at 6 p.m. and the title game will be at 7 p.m. 
Schlarman sixth at Beecher 
BEECHER — Janie Gross had 20 kills and was named to the All-Tournament team as the Hilltoppers beat Seneca 25-9, 25-0 and Momence 25-21, 25-16 and tied with Reed-Custer 25-19, 17-25 to take sixth at the Beecher Tournament. 
Arieal Scott also had 20 kills while Reagan Gifford had 11 kills and Elly Sermersheim added nine. 
PREP GIRLS SWIMMING 
Danville second in meet 
NORMAL — Kelsie Lichtenberger was third in the 100 yard butterfly (1 minute, 14.09 seconds) and fourth in the 200 individual medley (2:41.63) as the Vikings took second in a meet with Normal Community and Normal West. 
CeCe Strader was third in the 50 freestyle (28.40) and fourth in the 100 backstroke (1:15.55) for Danville, while Abbi Cortapassi was fourth in the 200 freestyle (2:20.65) and fifth in the 100 freestyle (1:04.19) and Wynter Haas was fifth in the 100 breaststroke (1:29.43). 
PREP GIRLS TENNIS 
Danville duo ends up third 
CHAMPAIGN — The team of Lauren Ellis and Eryn Marble lost in semifinal action but rebounded in the third-place match of an IHSA tennis sectional. 
Ellis and Marble lost to eventual champion Mia Stipes and Caroline Waddell of St. Thomas More in the semifinals 6-2, 6-7 (7-9), 6-4 before beating Champaign Centennial’s Jacklyn Gunn and Jasmine Lee 6-3, 6-4. 
The team will play next week in the state tournament at Buffalo Grove.
